# Optional: backend URL baked into the frontend at BUILD time.
#
# This is a Vite build-time substitution (injected during `npm run build`),
# NOT a runtime override. Changing it after a build has no effect; rebuild.
#
# Precedence:
#   1. VITE_API_BASE_URL (this file / .env.local / build-time shell export)
#   2. Dev fallback   -> http://127.0.0.1:8000 (Vite dev server)
#   3. Prod fallback  -> "" (same-origin; relative /api/... — works behind
#                          Tailscale Serve, Cloudflare Tunnel, a custom
#                          domain, or the packaged binary that serves the
#                          UI and API on one port)
#
# Set this only when the built bundle must reach a backend on a DIFFERENT
# origin than the one serving the HTML. For local dev, the portable binary,
# and any reverse-proxied prod deployment, leave it unset.
VITE_API_BASE_URL=
